## 9. `comic_reader` — Vocal Variety and Character Voice

**Why it works:** Reading scripted dialogue trains prosodic range naturally — different characters require different pitch, pace, and volume. Comics make this concrete and visual. Drama-in-education research consistently shows script-based speaking builds vocal variety more effectively than open-ended speaking tasks.

